994... 94% 96% 94% 95%\n61 68% 66*4 Southern Ry gen 4s 1966........ 68 68% 67% 68%\nlAI M% 162% 100 Southern Rv lev 6%s 1966 101% 101% 101 101%\n44% 68% 89 Third Ave adj 6a 1960 41% 41% 89 40%\nom? 88 64% 88% Union Pacific Ist 4s 1947........ 98% 93% 92% 92%\nm 89 96% 66% Union Pacific cv 4s 1927 96 96 96% 96%\n1M 88 68 60% Virginian Ry Ist Bs 19SS 94 94% 94 94%\n101 98%' 66% 98% Wabash Ist Bs 1689 96% 96% 95% 96\n69 68% 65% 66% Western Maryland 4s 1966...... 67 68 56% 58\n88% 79% 88% 78 Weetera Pacific Ba 1946 79% 76% 79 79%\n1 BS% 76% fl 19% West Shore Ist 4a 2861 79\u00a3i 80 76% SO\nI .w-*\nFINANCIAL.\nSATURDAY MARKET\nIS Limy AFFAIR\nPrices Go Higher in Busiest\nTworHour Session Since\nLast Spring.\nSELLING WELL ABSORBED\nStewart-Warner Up 4 Points and\nUnited Fruit Over 6\u2014Sugars\nDo Better.\nBy the Associated Press\nNEW YORK. November S.\u2014Con\nstructive forces were again at work\nin today\u2019s stock market, the most\nactive half holiday session since last\nspring, with the result that prices\ncontinued their move to higher\nground after an early period of\nregularity. w\nFloor traders and others who had\nbought stocks for a turn following\ntho unexpected declaration of an ex\ntra dividend by the United StatA-\nSteel Corporation, continued to take\nprofits in the usual industrial lead\nerti, ail of which opened at conce?-\nsions. The offerings were well absorb\ned and the general list again head\nupward.\nMore New High Mortis.\nUnited States Steel. Baldwin aau\nStudebaker all reached new high\nlevels on the movement. SteeJ close**\nquarter higher at 9314, Baldwin\ntouched 124. but reacted to up\nand Studebaker showed a net\ngain of points St t 10114. American\nWoolen was another strong feature,\nclosing 1 higher at 74.\nStewart Warner advanced 4 points\non the reported closing of a large,\ncontract. Sugars were helped by tho\nresumption of dividends on Manat!.\ngains of 1 to 2 points being recorded\nby ay active issues. United Fruit\njumpfli 614 points. Some of the other\nstrong spots included Western Union.\nDavison Chemical, Pacific Telephone.\nRepublic Steel preferred. General\nElectric and Kelsay Wheel, all 01\nwhich advanced 2 points or mors.\nC. A O. Share* Take Stamp.\nRalls were mixed, a drop of. 1% in\nChesapeake and Ohio being one of\nthe outstanding developments in\nthat group. There were a few\nstrong spots, notably New Orleans.\nTexas and Mexico, Southern Pacific.\nWheeling and Lake Erie preferred\nand Lackawanna, all up a point or\nmore.\nForeign exchanges were again r\nheavy. Demand sterling duplicated\nits previous low of the year, J 4.45%,\nand German marks fell so low that\nmost of the large banks declined to\ndo any business in them. French\nfrancs held relatively steady at 5.76 V;\ncents.\nBank Reserve Decreases.\nThe weekly clearing house state\nment showed an increase of \u00a710.457,-\n000 in loans, discounts and invest\nments and an increase of $34,440,000\nin net demand deposits. Reserve of\nmember banks in the Federal Reserve\nBank decreased $31,043,000, while time\ndeposits fell off $14,385,000. Aggregate\nreserves totaled $488,551,000, leaving\na deficit in reserve of $13,349,570; a\ndecrease of $35,340,690 below the pre\nvious week/\nTRADING ON CURB\nIS MORE ACTIVE\nOil Stocks Irregular During Week\nIndustrial Issues Display\nStronger Tone.\nBy the Associated Press.\nNEW YORK, November 3.\u2014There\nwas a pronounced broadening tend\nency to the trading on the New York\nCurb Exchange all through the week\nreflecting a substantial increase in\noutside-interest and also accumulation\nof many issues by those concerned In\ntheir control. Petroleum stocks were\nirregular, several of them being\nbought because of special develop\nments.\nPrairie 013 and Gas following the\nannouncement of the acquisition of\nproducers and refiners moved up to\n190, but profit-taking sales caused a\nquick reaction to 174. from which\nthere was another upturn. Toward\nthe close of the week Mutual Oil\nwas bought and bid for on a largo\nscale in connection with the bring\ning in of Its well in the Powell field\nwith an initial flow, of 10,000 barrelt;.\nwhich was at once connected up with\nHumble and Magnolia Pipe lines.\nThe leading Standard Oil issues\nmoved within a comparatively narrow\nrange, but they also were in de\nmand and at times made vigorous ad\nvances. Royal Canadian Syndicate\nwas a feature in the low-priced group\nbecause of buying based on the re\nport of the president of the company\nabout the developments in the Sweet\nGrass Arch field.\nIndustrial stocks also showed\nstrength during a good part of the\nweek.\nWHEAT VALUES IMPROVE.\ni Strength in Other Markets Spreads\n1 to Grain Pit.\nCHICAGO. November 3.\u2014 Helped b>\nstrength In the cotton market and In\nstocks and by assumed likelihood\nI that the federal government soon\nI would take steps likely to lift grain\nI values, the price of wheat showed an\nupward trend today. Th\u00ae close was\nfirm. 14 to Ti net higher; December,\n1.07%a1.0T?i to 1.07%a1.07T4, and May.\n1.1214 to 1.12Ka1. 12%. Corn finished\nto 114 up, oats at V*aV4 to %a% gain\nand provisions varying from 10 de\ncline to a like advance.\nPurchasing for eastern account\nI started wheat upward at the opening\nand, although at times reactions were\nwitnessed, the bulls had an advantage\nall day. The buying of wheat was\nalso accelerated as a result of mes\nsages Indicating that President Com-\nIdge and his advisers were consid\nering comprehensive reports touching\nthe agricultural situation and the\nI wheat trade, and aiso was giving\n1 further attention to plans for fur\nnishlng wheat or flour to Germany.\nBears In the wheat market made\nI much of assertions that farmer\u00ae bad\ndisposed of a large part of this year's\nwheat crop, and that any plan which\nthe government might adopt for the\nenhancement of values would benefit\nthe growers lees than was implied\nin current talk.\nCLOTH LIKELY TO GO UP.\nHigher Prices on Dry Goods Art\nExpected Soon.\nNEW YORK, November B.\u2014O\u00bbttou\ngoods market steady, showed a firm\nand advancing tendency, and new\nprices on higher levels were expected\n1 soon on several linos of finished\nj goods. Lonsdale and Blackatone 4*\u20144\n1 bleached goods were advanced te 17\ni cents a net. Trading was quieter\nI than was expected after the sharp\ncotton advance.\nI In men\u2019s wear lines concessions\ni were made to move stock lota of fab\nrlcs of a seasonable character. Fine\ndress specialties in flannel and fancy\ntwill conductions sold well for\nspring. Raw silk was somewhat\nsteadier and firmer. Linens wen\nsteady and quiet.\nPennsylvania has mors women 1:\nits legislature than any other state\nia the Union.","height":"24816","width":"19431"}}
